casebody.data:
GERBERDING v. TAHASH, WARDEN. No. 1059,

Misc.

Decided May 15, 1967. Petitioner pro se.t Douglas M. Head, Attorney General of Minnesota, William J. Hempel, Deputy Attorney General, and Gerard W. Snell, Acting Solicitor General, for respondent. Per Curiam.

The motion for leave to proceed in forma pauperis and the petition for a writ of certiorari are granted. The judgment is reversed. Jackson v. Denno, 378 U. S. 368.
